3x Grammy award-winning superstar, Lizzo has become a household name with over 5 billion global streams and a platinum selling debut album to date. With the help of anthemic smash hits like the 7x Platinum ‚ÄúTruth Hurts,‚Äù the 3x Platinum ‚ÄúGood As Hell,‚Äù and the 2x Platinum ‚ÄúJuice,‚Äù Lizzo released her Nice Life Recording Company/Atlantic Records debut album CUZ I LOVE YOU on April 19th 2019, debuting at #6 on the Billboard Top 200 Albums chart and spending 24 consecutive weeks in the chart‚Äôs Top 10. ‚ÄúTruth Hurts‚Äù became the longest running #1 by a solo female rap artist in history after spending seven weeks atop the charts. Since the release of the meteoric CUZ I LOVE YOU, Lizzo has been named both Time Magazine and Entertainment Weekly‚Äôs 2019 Entertainer of the Year as well as gracing the covers of Rolling Stone, Billboard‚Äôs GRAMMY Preview Issue, British Vogue, Elle‚Äôs Women In Music Issue, and many others.  Additionally, Lizzo kicked off 2020 with a showstopping opening performance at the 62nd Annual GRAMMY awards and took home three big wins, in addition to being the most-nominated artist of the year. 2020 has also seen her win the awards for Best Female R&B/Pop Artist at the 2020 B.E.T Awards and both ‚ÄúEntertainer of the Year‚Äù and ‚ÄúOutstanding Video‚Äù at the 2020 NAACP Awards. Her list of high profile TV performances also include the 2019 American Music Awards, VMAs, B.E.T Awards and Saturday Night Live, in addition to in depth profiles on CBS This Morning‚Äôs GRAMMY primetime special and CBS Sunday Morning. Now, Lizzo returns with her first new single in two years- the highly-anticipated ‚ÄúRumors" featuring Cardi B.

title: HERE IS WHY MESSI REJECTED NEYMAR‚ÄôS OFFER and chose ‚Ññ30 shirt at PSG!
description:
HERE IS WHY MESSI REJECTED NEYMAR‚ÄôS OFFER and chose ‚Ññ30 shirt at PSG!

Hello guys! Lionel Messi is now officially a PSG player! 
The signing, his presentation and the official announcement - all of that is settled and the biggest transfer of this summer has been finally made!

One of the most intriguing moments in Messi‚Äôs transfer is his shirt number. Many people expected Leo to accept Neymar‚Äôs offer to take his number 10 jersey or that he‚Äôd choose number 19 that Messi wore for two seasons at Barcelona, but none of that has happened. The Argentinian eventually chose number 30, and it‚Äôs not a random choice whatsoever! For the legendary striker, this number is special for many reasons, and today we‚Äôre going to talk about it in detail!

Guys, we‚Äôre very excited to start releasing new videos more actively, and we hope you‚Äôll appreciate our efforts by liking and subscribing to our channel.
Let's roll!

Friendship with Deco and Ronaldinho

The well-known fact: Lionel Messi is a quiet and humble guy outside the pitch, and it has always been so! At a young age, the ‚Äúshy‚Äù Argentinian showed great promise, but still was far from the status of being a Barcelona legend, hence he needed the help and advice from experienced players. Barcelona‚Äôs first squad superstars at that period Ronaldinho and Deco, noticing Leo‚Äôs great potential and desire to learn, took care of the young guy.

 The Brazilian duo helped young Messi in many important cases. For example, they often drove him to training sessions, invited him to their table during lunches at the base, and, of course, were helping him with valuable advice on the pitch.

As soon as Lionel became good enough to make his debut for the first squad, he still had to decide on the shirt number, and, being grateful to his mentors, he chose the number 30 as a sum of their numbers. Ronaldinho performed under the number 10, and Deco wore a shirt number 20.
That‚Äôs a very interesting approach!
This was not the only respectful gesture on the part of Messi, by the way. Lionel saved Deco‚Äôs shirt in his home collection, and he always remembered Ronaldinho‚Äôs mentoring with great appreciation.

"Ronaldinho helped me a lot. I came into the dressing room at 16-17 years of age, seeing all those footballing giants made it tough. But he mentored me and made me feel comfortable, and I loosened up. Afterwards on the pitch, I always looked for him,‚Äù Lionel was saying.
And that‚Äôs how it has to be ‚Äî modesty, discipline, hard work, and gratitude!

Debut for Barcelona

We mentioned Messi‚Äôs debut for Barcelona for a reason. This is another crucial factor that made number 30 very important for Leo.

On October 16th, 2004, ‚ÄúLa Pulga‚Äù played his first professional game for the ‚ÄúBlaugrana‚Äù first team. It was the Catalan derby against Espanyol, in which Barcelona head coach Frank Rijkaard substituted the only goalscorer in the game Deco for Messi to come out at the end of the second half. That night, the newcomer with number 30 on his back for the first time felt the senior football and realized what it is to be involved in the first team success. 

Remarkably, current PSG head coach Mauricio Pochettino, who is going to work with Lionel for the next few years, also took part in that memorable derby as an Espanyol player. This is how ironic the football world can sometimes be.

First goal for Barcelona

30 is also the number that associates Messi with his first goal for Barca! On May 1st, 2005, in La Liga round 34, the ‚ÄúBlaugrana‚Äù played against Albacete at home. In the 88th minute with a score of 1-0 in favour of the Catalans, Rijkaard gave another chance to 17-years-old Leo having substituted Samuel Eto‚Äôo who scored that only goal at the time.  
Two minutes later, the young Argentinian received an exquisite chip pass and scored by no less exquisite lob to set the score to 2-0. 

Since that day, Messi managed to score 671 goals to become the greatest player in Barcelona history, though his first goal was probably the most memorable and special, because that's how the legend was born - that minute and with this number on his back.

The first Champions League victory

The new chapter at PSG

Dear friends, thank you so much for watching. Stay with us, and don‚Äôt miss out on our new videos! It was a Top Football channel. Bye-bye!

channelDescription:
Rocket science. A term we all use to describe something incredibly difficult. Trying to grasp all of the concepts involved in rocket science can be incredibly intimidating.

My name‚Äôs Tim Dodd but I'm better known as the Everyday Astronaut. Recently I fell head over heals in love with spaceflight. My appreciation and curiosity for the subject grew into an obsession. Before you knew it, all I wanted to do was learn more and more. And the more I learned, the more I wanted to share what was making me so excited. 

But as someone who dropped out of college and has no technical background or degree‚Ä¶ I really felt unqualified for the job of explaining rocket science to anyone. But the fact of the matter is, if I can learn this stuff, anyone can. 

Rocket science is awesome, and you don‚Äôt need to be a rocket scientist to be excited. 

Everyday Astronaut. Bringing space down to Earth for everyday people.
